<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Motion Data</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Kinematic data</keyword>
    <keyword>Motion Data<keyword>Acceleration</keyword><keyword>Angle</keyword><keyword>Position</keyword><keyword>Velocity</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Motion-Values</text>: values of Displacement, Velocity, Acceleration and Jerk for a Linear or Angular dimension, as a function of the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Master-Machine-Angle" styleclass="Popup Box2">Master-Machine-Angle</link>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Motions-values from </text><text styleclass="Popup Box2">MotionDesigner</text>: are specified by the user to give the motion-values (Y-axis) as a function an independent variable (X-axis).</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">When a Motion from <text styleclass="Popup Box2">MotionDesigner</text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">&#32;</text>is given to a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> that is identified by a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion-Dimension FB</text>, the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> is known as a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Motion-Driven-Part" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion-Part</link>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">When a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Motion from</text><text styleclass="Popup Box2"> MotionDesigner</text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">&#32;</text>is given to a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> identified by a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion-Path FB</text>, the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text> is known as a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Motion-Driven-Point" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion-Point</link>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Motion (general definition)</text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">: </text>the movement of a Part, or Point, when the motion-values are a function of an independent variable. The independent variable might itself change in a simple or complex way. </para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Motion-Driven-Part">Motion-Part</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Motion-Driven-Point">Motion-Point</link>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
